uproar /ˈʌpˌrɔː/

1. N-UNCOUNT If there is uproar , there is a lot of shouting and noise because people are very angry or upset about something. 骚动 [also 'a' N, oft 'in' N] 

例： The announcement caused uproar in the crowd. 公告在人群中引起了一阵骚动。 

2. N-UNCOUNT You can also use uproar to refer to a lot of public criticism and debate about something that has made people angry. 哗然 [also 'a' N] 

例： The town is in uproar over the dispute. 该城对此争端一片哗然。

